Project notes

This repository was assembled as the public-facing component of the JPG2151: GIS & Society applied project.

The workflow moved through multiple stages:
- data gathering and alignment,
- tract-level indicator preparation,
- CCNI construction,
- interactive Leaflet mapping,
- final GitHub Pages publication.

Software used
- Python / Google Colab in earlier exploratory stages
- R and RStudio for final data handling and mapping
- Leaflet for the interactive web map
- GitHub and GitHub Pages for public sharing

Final repository purpose
This repository is intended to show the simplified workflow, final outputs, and key resource notes behind the Toronto Climate Canopy Need Index project.

StoryMap was not included in the final submission.

